The paper deals with competitive analysis, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) that studies the performance of algorithms in competitive scenarios. The paper also involves the study of online algorithms, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of past experience and random sampling is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the study of the secretary problem is a classic problem in decision theory and optimization, which is often studied in machine learning (cs.LG).
